# HTML Style Guide

*This rule automatically attaches when working with HTML files.*

## Structure

- Use HTML5 semantic elements (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
- Maintain consistent indentation (2 or 4 spaces)
- Use lowercase for all HTML tags and attributes
- Always quote attribute values
- Use self-closing tags for void elements (`<img />`, `<br />`, `<hr />`)

## Script and Style Placement

- **CSS**: In `<head>` section, prefer external files
- **JavaScript**: At bottom of `<body>`, prefer external files
- Use `defer` or `async` for non-blocking scripts when appropriate
- Avoid inline JavaScript and CSS unless absolutely necessary

## Accessibility

- Always include `alt` attributes for images
- Use proper heading hierarchy (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`)
- Use semantic HTML for better screen reader support
- Include ARIA labels when needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works

## Template Integration

- Keep HTML structure consistent across pages
- Use consistent class naming (follow BEM or your chosen methodology)
- Document template variables clearly
- Separate content from presentation

## Example Structure

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Page Title</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <!-- Header content -->
  </header>
  
  <main>
    <!-- Main content -->
  </main>
  
  <footer>
    <!-- Footer content -->
  </footer>
  
  <script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

